Calculate Jenks Breakpoints for Social Network Data

get_breakpoints.Rd

This function computes Jenks natural breakpoints for social network data across individuals and time points. The result is a matrix containing breakpoints for each individual at each time point.

Usage

get_breakpoints(social_networks, sex = NA, break_num = 3)

Arguments

social_networks

A 3D array with dimensions Dimensions: individuals, individuals, time points.

sex

The sex information of the zebra finches in social networks. Default is NA.

break_num

The number of breaks (clusters) to compute. Default is 3.

Value

A matrix containing the ID, time point, and Jenks breakpoints for each individual-time combination.

Examples

# Assuming 'social_network_data' is a 3D array with dimensions

sex = sex.information, break_num = 3)
